T02954393&#x00026;rank=1</ext-link>.</p></sec></ack><notes notes-type="author-contribution"><title>Authors&#x02019; contributions</title><p>The clinical study is being conducted thanks to the contribution of MF: she designed the study and will conduct the data analysis. She is also the general study coordinator, UNG center coordinator and participated in the development of this manuscript. BR-V is responsible for the recruitment of the participants, clinical evaluation, microbiological and immunological sample collection and maintenance of the participants in the UNG center. She also participated in the development of this manuscript. MJM performs the periodontal treatment of the participants in the UNG center. LCdeF will be responsible for processing the microbiological samples. MF will help in the data analysis. PMD will be responsible for processing the immunological samples. AF helps in the periodontal maintenance of the participants in the UNG center. EF helps in the recruitment of the participants and microbiological and immunological sample collection in the UNG center. MLSS is responsible for the recruitment of the participants, periodontal treatment, microbiological and immunological sample collection and maintenance of the participants in the USP-SP center. MdeF performs the periodontal treatment of the participants in the USP-SP center. MG performs the periodontal treatment of the participants in the USP-SP center. LS is responsible for the clinical evaluation in the USP-SP center. GAR participated in the development of this manuscript. CMP is the USP-SP center coordinator and participated in the development of this manuscript. All authors read and approved the final manuscript.</p></notes><notes notes-type="COI-statement"><sec id="FPar3"><title>Ethics approval and consent to participate</title><p id="Par60">The authors declare that the Guarulhos University Clinical Research Ethics Committee (CAAE: 32.465.714.4.1001.5506) and University of S&#x000e3;o Pau